AB  - In this paper, we collect detailed information on the budget institutions of Latin American countries. We classify these institutions on a `hierarchical'/`collegial' scale, as a function of the existence of constraints on the deficit, and voting rules. We show that `hierarchical' and transparent procedures have been associated with more fiscal discipline in Latin America in the 1980s and early 1990s.
